sence, they would not be able to return home as they are no longer visible to such ships.&#10;&#10;The mysterious object that Willard observes heading toward the Mary Lou is also a Ghost Ship, an old-fashioned rocket ship that has been drifting in space for many years and appears faint and ghost-like due to its mass and energy being gradually drained over time. Its crew may be unaware of their changed state, as they remain real to themselves but not to other ships that have not been in space for more than fifteen years.&#10;&#10;Therefore, the anguish felt by Willard and Dobbin is primarily caused by their extreme loneliness and isolation in space, and they may never be able to return to Earth due to their current state of existence making them invisible to Earth ships.">
