uld represent a blurring of the line between reality and hallucination during space exploration, where the relative nature of matter and the extreme conditions can cause objects and perceptions to become less real or solid.&#10;4. His reflections on these experiences highlight his struggle with isolation and loneliness, as well as his questioning of reason and the limits of understanding in the face of space's mysteries.&#10;5. The Ghost Ship and the voices could symbolize both the allure and danger of venturing into the unknown, representing the fragility of human existence amidst the vast cosmos.">
